Introduced Version
SENATE BILL No. 18
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 20-23-17.2.
Synopsis: East Chicago school board elections. Changes the election
process for the governing body of the East Chicago school corporation,
so that all members are elected at large by the voters of the school
corporation. (Current law provides that three members are elected from
certain districts, and two members are elected at large.) Makes
conforming changes.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Randolph Lonnie M
December 8, 2025, read first time and referred to Committee on Elections.
