A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
education.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 20-23-17.2-3.1, AS AMENDED BY P.L.195-2025,
2 SECTION 35, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 3.1. (a) The governing body of the school
4 corporation consists of five (5) members, elected as provided in this
5 chapter.
6 (b) Three (3) members shall be elected as follows:
7 (1) From districts established as provided in section 4.1 of this
8 chapter. At large by all the voters of the school corporation.
9 (2) At the general election held in the county in 2026, 2030, 2034,
10 2038, 2042, and every four (4) years thereafter.
11 (c) Two (2) members shall be elected as follows:
12 (1) At large by all the voters of the school corporation.
13 (2) At the general election held in the county in 2028, 2032, 2036,
14 2040, 2044, and every four (4) years thereafter.
15 (d) The term of office of a member of the governing body:
16 (1) is four (4) years; and
17 (2) begins January 1 after the election of members of the
