5 SECTION 2. IC 20-23-17.2-4.1 IS REPEALED [EFFECTIVE JULY
6 1, 2026]. Sec. 4.1. (a) As used in this section, "council district" refers
7 to a district of the city legislative body:
8 (1) established under IC 36-4-6-3; and
9 (2) as in effect on January 1, 2015.
10 (b) The districts from which a member of the governing body is
11 elected under section 3.1(b) of this chapter are as follows:
12 (1) School corporation district 1 consists of the territory formed
13 by council district 1 and council district 2.
14 (2) School corporation district 2 consists of the territory formed
15 by council district 3 and council district 4.
16 (3) School corporation district 3 consists of the territory formed
17 by council district 5 and council district 6.
18 SECTION 3. IC 20-23-17.2-5, AS AMENDED BY P.L.195-2025,
19 SECTION 36, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
20 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) The following apply to an election of
21 members of the governing body of the school corporation under section
22 3.1(b) of this chapter:
23 (1) Each candidate must file a petition of nomination with the
24 circuit court clerk not earlier than one hundred four (104) days
25 and not later than seventy-four (74) days before the general
26 election at which members are to be elected. The petition of
27 nomination must include the following information:
28 (A) The name of the candidate.
29 (B) The candidate's residence address and the district in which
30 the candidate resides.
31 (C) The signatures of at least twenty (20) registered voters
